    <item>
      <title>Version 0.5.0</title>
      <link>https://minrender.com/</link>
      <sparkle:version>0.5.0</sparkle:version>
      <sparkle:shortVersionString>0.5.0</sparkle:shortVersionString>
      <sparkle:os>windows</sparkle:os>
      <description><![CDATA[
      <h3>minRender 0.5.0</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><b>Frame preview</b> — click frames or chunks in the grid to preview rendered EXR/PNG/TIFF output right in the monitor, with an EXR layer picker. Works from any node.</li>
        <li><b>Edit Job</b> — change a submitted job's parameters and apply to the next chunks, restart in-flight work, or start over. Edits are acknowledged by the leader and queue to the farm share if it's unreachable.</li>
        <li><b>Stop chunk &amp; resubmit</b> — stop a chunk (its frames leave the progress accounting; the job finishes "partial") and resubmit it as a new job with different parameters, e.g. one frame per node.</li>
        <li><b>UI overhaul</b> — tabbed detail pane, modal submission, resizable columns, durations, selectable node rows, async farm cleanup with per-section select-all, and a Show in Finder button for logs.</li>
        <li><b>Farm reliability</b> — nodes advertise capabilities across versions; a render fence prevents double-rendered frames after edits or connection flaps; VPN-friendly timeouts stop remote nodes from being flagged dead.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Rolling upgrade safe: older nodes keep working unchanged; version-dependent features stay disabled until the leader updates.</p>
      ]]></description>
